title.narrative: HPN - Afya UGAVI: Global Health Supply Chain - Procurement and Supply Management Technical Assistance

description.narrative: (Kenya): .The Afya Ugavi supports the Ministry of Health's (MOH) Division of Health Products and Medical Technologies (HPMT), National health programs and priority malaria endemic counties to strengthen the management of supply chain systems. Additionally, this activity is advancing Kenya's commitment to commodity security as part of the county's journey to self-reliance. The Afya Ugavi uses a maturity index tool to supply chain systems in target counties to define the technical assistance needs. ..Technical assistance to the HPMT Division includes strengthening the supply chain governance for policy, strategy, standards, and guidelines. It also includes rational replenishment of commodities through enhanced commodity data visibility and steward management of health commodities. The national supply and logistics system is undergoing optimization to redefine inventory policies for MOH. In FY 2020, Afya Ugavi will continue strengthening the National Malaria Program governance, coordination and leadership for supply chain management for malaria commodities. There is increased focus (in targeted counties) on stewardship for accountability of USAID-funded commodities through improved commodity tracking, inventory management, and supply chain audits. In strengthening health supply chain systems, the activity aligns with the United States foreign policy by demonstrating the U.S.A's strong leadership and influence in global health, while advancing American values saving lives and improving health...
